reviewText: As a hardcore Gilbert & Sullivan fan this is one of the best parodies of G & S that I have seen. It followed H M S Pinafore quite well, yet adhered to the beliefs and needs of the San Francisco Gay Men's Chorus. I will watch and rewatch this production many many times.
I saw this at the Cambridge Public Library, movie night I thoroughly enjoyed it. It is clever, and the talent superb! I raced home to purchase it the same night!!
